00:32:45,647 --> 00:32:47,414
(OWL HOOTING)

250
00:32:54,056 --> 00:32:56,122
Oh, great.

251
00:33:16,879 --> 00:33:18,146
(SHIVERING)

252
00:33:25,320 --> 00:33:27,346
(PHONE BEEPING)

253
00:33:30,092 --> 00:33:31,827
Shit!

254
00:33:32,227 --> 00:33:34,127
Shit!

255
00:33:41,870 --> 00:33:43,739
(PANTING)

256
00:33:43,939 --> 00:33:44,867
(GRUNTS)

257
00:33:53,248 --> 00:33:55,114
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

258
00:34:25,881 --> 00:34:27,549
Oh.

259
00:34:29,852 --> 00:34:32,488
- Good boy.
- (SHADOW WHINING)

260
00:34:32,788 --> 00:34:35,355
Good boy. Yeah.

261
00:34:39,995 --> 00:34:42,030
You're lucky you had the dog.

262
00:34:42,130 --> 00:34:46,069
It was because of his persistent barking
last night that I even bothered to come over.

263
00:34:47,169 --> 00:34:49,571
How's your head? You must
have a hell of a headache.

264
00:34:49,671 --> 00:34:51,473
How did you get in here?

265
00:34:51,573 --> 00:34:54,476
Well, that would be your keys.

266
00:34:55,060 --> 00:34:57,146
- Give me those.
- Uh-uh.

267
00:34:57,246 --> 00:34:59,579
- Give me my fucking keys.
- Easy!

268
00:35:04,519 --> 00:35:06,288
Oh, what are you gonna do with that?

269
00:35:06,388 --> 00:35:08,023
I swear to God, if you don't
give me my fucking keys,

270
00:35:08,123 --> 00:35:10,526
I'm gonna beat the shit out of you!

271
00:35:10,626 --> 00:35:12,461
Okay. All right.

272
00:35:12,561 --> 00:35:15,357
Take your keys.
Nobody's threatening you.

273
00:35:15,457 --> 00:35:17,960
Bullshit! You... you knocked me out
and you dragged me here to...

274
00:35:18,060 --> 00:35:19,701
- To do what?
- I don't know.

275
00:35:19,801 --> 00:35:21,904
I saw you running around last night.

276
00:35:22,004 --> 00:35:25,939
You recognized me, you tripped over a rock,
you cracked your own head.

277
00:35:28,543 --> 00:35:32,348
And the stuff on the wall,
you... you put it there, didn't you?

278
00:35:32,948 --> 00:35:35,282
What the hell are you talking about?

279
00:35:43,292 --> 00:35:45,725
Any idea what it means?

280
00:35:59,641 --> 00:36:00,907
Come out here.

281
00:36:03,345 --> 00:36:05,648
Take a look at this.

282
00:36:06,477 --> 00:36:08,248
These are all the same.

283
00:36:15,724 --> 00:36:19,294
3-0-2-12.

284
00:36:19,394 --> 00:36:22,843
It's a date. March 2nd,

285
00:36:22,943 --> 00:36:24,987
2012.

286
00:36:25,567 --> 00:36:27,402
What?

287
00:36:27,702 --> 00:36:29,137
Who did this?

288
00:36:29,937 --> 00:36:32,574
- I thought you did.
- Why would I do this?

289
00:36:32,674 --> 00:36:34,865
I don't know. I mean, you're the only one
out here. I just assumed.

290
00:36:34,965 --> 00:36:37,077
- I gotta go.
- What does it mean?

291
00:36:37,177 --> 00:36:38,328
- I don't know.
- Yes, you do.

292
00:36:38,428 --> 00:36:41,635
- I don't know.
- Okay, wait, just... (SIGHS)

293
00:36:41,950 --> 00:36:44,717
Look, you don't have to talk
about it, all right?

294
00:36:45,687 --> 00:36:47,446
Will you just...

295
00:36:47,546 --> 00:36:49,864
will you just stay
until it gets light out?

296
00:36:50,639 --> 00:36:52,992
I don't feel safe here.

297
00:37:30,732 --> 00:37:32,599
(EXHALES)

298
00:38:21,149 --> 00:38:23,016
(BIRDS CHIRPING)

299
00:38:44,339 --> 00:38:46,106
Hi.

300
00:38:48,276 --> 00:38:50,345
How you feeling?

301
00:38:51,371 --> 00:38:53,415
What time is it?

302
00:38:53,515 --> 00:38:55,617
3:00 in the afternoon.

303
00:38:55,717 --> 00:38:58,050
You slept quite a while.

304
00:38:58,987 --> 00:39:01,490
What happened to your head?

305
00:39:01,590 --> 00:39:03,464
Did you see the numbers?

306
00:39:04,659 --> 00:39:08,361
- What numbers?
- In the bedroom on the window.

307
00:39:09,798 --> 00:39:14,436
No, I didn't see any numbers.
I saw the trash bags. I took them down.

308
00:39:14,536 --> 00:39:17,069
Was it too bright in there for you?

309
00:39:27,616 --> 00:39:29,815
This is ridiculous.

310
00:39:32,921 --> 00:39:35,090
(PAUL SIGHS) Anna.

311
00:39:35,190 --> 00:39:37,659
- It was all over the place.
- Listen.

312
00:39:37,759 --> 00:39:40,495
There were no numbers on the windows.
There were just a couple of trash bags.

313
00:39:40,595 --> 00:39:42,931
- I took them down, that's all.
- You don't believe me.

314
00:39:43,031 --> 00:39:45,600
No, it's not that I don't believe you.

315
00:39:45,700 --> 00:39:47,436
I don't know, maybe you had
another nightmare.

316
00:39:47,536 --> 00:39:50,872
It wasn't a nightmare, Paul!
It was a date. March 2nd, 2012.

317
00:39:50,972 --> 00:39:54,209
- It was all over!
- Look, stop! Anna, please.

318
00:39:54,309 --> 00:39:56,712
This has gone too far now.

319
00:39:56,812 --> 00:40:01,183
- Does that date mean anything to you?
- No, it doesn't.

320
00:40:01,583 --> 00:40:05,220
You know what? Ask your housekeeper
or groundskeeper, whatever he was.

321
00:40:05,320 --> 00:40:07,022
- He was here. He saw it.
- What, Jeremy?

322
00:40:07,122 --> 00:40:10,358
- Yeah, I think that's what his name was.
- What was he doing here?

323
00:40:10,458 --> 00:40:14,260
That's what I've been trying to tell you.
He helped me! He...

324
00:40:16,431 --> 00:40:20,333
Okay, pack up your things, get ready
to leave. I'm gonna talk to Jeremy now.

325
00:40:23,505 --> 00:40:25,298
(DOOR OPENS, CLOSES)

326
00:41:08,183 --> 00:41:10,043
Jeremy.

327
00:41:20,629 --> 00:41:21,895
(COMPUTER CHIRPING)

328
00:41:43,118 --> 00:41:45,139
(COMPUTER KEYS CLICKING)

329
00:41:52,227 --> 00:41:54,260
I saw your little trick
with the graffiti.

330
00:42:06,474 --> 00:42:09,308
You can't hide from me, Jeremy!

331
00:42:13,214 --> 00:42:14,816
You try another stunt like that,

332
00:42:15,116 --> 00:42:18,386
I'll have immigration
send you back to Canada.

333
00:42:18,486 --> 00:42:19,619
Little wanker.

334
00:43:05,033 --> 00:43:06,799
(GASPS)

335
00:43:42,003 --> 00:43:43,823
(GASPING)

336
00:43:55,183 --> 00:43:57,050
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

337
00:44:20,975 --> 00:44:22,809
(GASPING)

338
00:44:26,314 --> 00:44:27,781
(COMPUTER CHIRPING)

339
00:44:31,085 --> 00:44:32,794
(COMPUTER KEYS CLICKING)

340
00:44:33,922 --> 00:44:35,352
(COMPUTER BEEPS)

341
00:45:04,519 --> 00:45:07,286
PAUL: Hey, Anna, are you in there?

342
00:45:09,157 --> 00:45:11,526
Uh, yeah.

343
00:45:11,626 --> 00:45:16,428
- Are these bags ready to go now?
- Yeah, you can pack 'em.

344
00:45:17,732 --> 00:45:19,899
Oh, listen, have you seen the key
to the boiler room?

345
00:45:21,169 --> 00:45:23,378
- The what?
- The key for the boiler room.

346
00:45:23,478 --> 00:45:25,206
I need to turn the furnace off
before we go.

347
00:45:25,306 --> 00:45:27,015
Wait.

348
00:45:27,842 --> 00:45:29,511
- I haven't seen them.
- Really?

349
00:45:29,711 --> 00:45:31,377
They're not in your jeans or something?

350
00:45:33,114 --> 00:45:35,183
Hold on a second. I'll be right there.

351
00:45:35,847 --> 00:45:37,914
All right.

352
00:45:52,200 --> 00:45:53,835
Oh, listen, would you mind
hurrying up a little bit?

353
00:45:53,935 --> 00:45:56,237
I don't wanna get snagged up
in rush hour traffic.

354
00:45:56,337 --> 00:45:58,370
Actually...

355
00:45:59,340 --> 00:46:02,341
- Ah, here they are.
- Why don't we stay?

356
00:46:28,536 --> 00:46:30,302
(ANNA GRUNTING)

357
00:47:42,143 --> 00:47:43,981
(GASPS)

358
00:47:44,812 --> 00:47:46,879
(BREATHING SHALLOWLY)

359
00:48:09,407 --> 00:48:11,170
Paul?

360
00:48:13,841 --> 00:48:16,909
Oh, hey. Morning.

361
00:48:18,212 --> 00:48:20,581
So why did you sleep
on the couch last night?

362
00:48:20,681 --> 00:48:22,584
Was I that bad in bed?

363
00:48:22,684 --> 00:48:25,420
No, I, uh... I just couldn't sleep.

364
00:48:25,520 --> 00:48:29,722
- Nightmares again?
- No, thank God.

365
00:49:16,838 --> 00:49:19,512
- All right, I won't be long.
- Okay, I'm gonna go and get gas.

366
00:49:19,612 --> 00:49:21,306
Okay.

367
00:49:33,487 --> 00:49:35,321
(MUSIC PLAYING)

368
00:49:56,877 --> 00:49:57,943
Excuse me.

369
00:50:00,548 --> 00:50:02,483
- More coffee?
- Uh, no, thanks.

370
00:50:02,583 --> 00:50:06,654
I'm sorry, this might seem a bit random,
but do you know this woman?

371
00:50:06,954 --> 00:50:09,491
She built a modern style glass
house out here,

372
00:50:09,591 --> 00:50:12,108
about 10 miles north
of the old Gamma Ranch.

373
00:50:14,762 --> 00:50:18,797
You may want to talk to Joe over there.
He knows everyone in town.

374
00:50:20,001 --> 00:50:21,767
Thanks.

375
00:50:22,637 --> 00:50:24,603
(CHATTER)

376
00:50:26,807 --> 00:50:28,941
Excuse me.

377
00:50:29,959 --> 00:50:32,113
I'm sorry to bother you, but, um...

378
00:50:32,213 --> 00:50:35,617
my name's Anna and I'm looking
for someone from around here.

379
00:50:35,717 --> 00:50:38,551
The bartender said
that you might be able to help.

380
00:50:43,524 --> 00:50:47,942
I'm staying at the glass house.
It's 10 miles north. You know it?

381
00:50:48,629 --> 00:50:51,499
Yeah, I know that house. What about it?

382
00:50:52,199 --> 00:50:55,269
I'm looking for the architect,
Vera Palm.

383
00:50:55,369 --> 00:50:56,969
Does that ring any bells?

384
00:51:05,846 --> 00:51:07,132
Let's talk outside.

385
00:51:18,926 --> 00:51:20,995
I know her housekeeper.

386
00:51:21,595 --> 00:51:23,464
- Jeremy?
- Yes. He...

387
00:51:23,564 --> 00:51:27,168
- comes in for guidance now and then.
- What sort of guidance?

388
00:51:27,268 --> 00:51:31,172
For $39 a session, you can find out.

389
00:51:31,272 --> 00:51:36,110
I also offer a lot of original
healing stones and native artwork.

390
00:51:36,210 --> 00:51:38,577
My shop is right over there.

391
00:51:41,749 --> 00:51:43,718
I think this has been
a misunderstanding.

392
00:51:44,318 --> 00:51:45,551
Are you sure?

393
00:51:48,156 --> 00:51:50,224
Hey, Anna, you ready?

394
00:51:50,624 --> 00:51:52,527
Look, I'm just trying to find
this woman.

395
00:51:52,827 --> 00:51:55,094
Well, you can't. She's missing.

396
00:51:56,030 --> 00:51:57,196
Since when?

397
00:51:59,867 --> 00:52:02,870
- Last March.
- Wait, what happened?

398
00:52:03,270 --> 00:52:05,804
JOE: Number's on the card.

399
00:52:27,862 --> 00:52:30,328
Oh, it's freezing in here.

400
00:52:32,366 --> 00:52:34,635
Why don't you take a little nap?

401
00:52:34,735 --> 00:52:38,873
Then when you wake up,
I can grill up some of these, uh...

402
00:52:39,173 --> 00:52:42,040
juicy local steaks I keep hearing about.

403
00:52:42,743 --> 00:52:45,940
You know, I'm really glad
we decided to stay in the end.

404
00:52:46,040 --> 00:52:47,846
(FIRE CRACKLING)

405
00:52:49,950 --> 00:52:51,317
Why did you lie to me?

406
00:52:53,020 --> 00:52:54,322
What?

407
00:52:54,922 --> 00:52:58,224
Don't, Paul. Why did you lie to me?

408
00:52:59,160 --> 00:53:01,028
(SIGHS)

409
00:53:01,228 --> 00:53:04,232
And there was me thinking we might
have a nice, quiet evening together.

410
00:53:04,382 --> 00:53:08,906
- You know what happened on March 2nd.
- Who have you been talking to now?

411
00:53:09,006 --> 00:53:13,605
Doesn't matter. What matters is you didn't
tell me the truth and I wanna know why.

412
00:53:14,441 --> 00:53:15,636
(SCOFFS)

413
00:53:15,736 --> 00:53:19,610
Okay, uh... the truth is
I didn't want to scare you.

414
00:53:20,181 --> 00:53:22,583
It can be pretty intimidating out here
when you're by yourself.

415
00:53:23,171 --> 00:53:26,120
I just didn't wanna fuel
your vivid imagination

416
00:53:26,220 --> 00:53:29,757
with legends about
disappearing people in the desert.

417
00:53:30,057 --> 00:53:32,527
Well, if it's just an urban legend,
then why not tell me?

418
00:53:32,627 --> 00:53:34,360
Because that's what they are.
They're just...

419
00:53:39,800 --> 00:53:41,566
(SIGHS)

420
00:53:41,666 --> 00:53:42,742
Okay.

421
00:53:44,138 --> 00:53:47,806
The designer of this house,
the architect of this house...

422
00:53:48,709 --> 00:53:51,045
got lost in the desert.

423
00:53:51,245 --> 00:53:54,315
She went for a hike and never came back.

424
00:53:54,415 --> 00:53:59,616
Apparently it happens all the time.
People get lost, but she didn't come back.

425
00:54:00,521 --> 00:54:04,125
- And you're saying you didn't know her.
- Well, how would I?

426
00:54:04,305 --> 00:54:07,328
(SCOFFS) I don't believe you.

427
00:54:07,828 --> 00:54:09,599
Anna.

428
00:54:14,068 --> 00:54:16,771
I'm getting worried about you now, Anna.

429
00:54:16,871 --> 00:54:18,928
It's... it's somewhere down here.

430
00:54:23,978 --> 00:54:27,014
- Well, I guess you cleaned it out.
- The photograph? Yes, I did.

431
00:54:27,214 --> 00:54:28,549
Because you didn't want me
to see her with you.

432
00:54:28,649 --> 00:54:31,219
Of course I didn't want you
to see me with my ex.

433
00:54:31,952 --> 00:54:34,789
I wouldn't want to see photographs of you
lying around with your ex either.

434
00:54:35,189 --> 00:54:38,891
You're hiding something from me. And don't
just keep blaming it on my vivid imagination.

435
00:54:40,161 --> 00:54:43,264
Oh, really, Anna? Because considering
your history of mental illness...

436
00:54:43,364 --> 00:54:46,417
Nightmares are not
a mental illness, Paul!

437
00:54:46,517 --> 00:54:48,002
Well...

438
00:54:48,102 --> 00:54:51,069
judging by the amount
of medication you're tak...

439
00:54:55,609 --> 00:54:57,376
I know what I've seen.

440
00:55:06,287 --> 00:55:08,854
I made a terrible mistake.

441
00:55:12,460 --> 00:55:13,492
What?

442
00:55:19,466 --> 00:55:21,833
You're right about one thing.

443
00:55:24,305 --> 00:55:26,344
I've been hiding something from you.

444
00:55:30,344 --> 00:55:35,114
I couldn't just watch you pounding
these things down day after day.

445
00:55:36,517 --> 00:55:38,759
They're placebos.

446
00:55:40,788 --> 00:55:43,457
At least you've been having plenty
of vitamin C the last few days.

447
00:55:43,657 --> 00:55:45,593
You switched out my pills?

448
00:55:46,466 --> 00:55:48,218
Yeah.

449
00:55:49,196 --> 00:55:51,864
That's why you've been having
such extreme reactions.

450
00:55:54,769 --> 00:55:57,004
I'm sorry. I thought you could...

451
00:55:57,104 --> 00:55:59,340
do without them.

452
00:55:59,440 --> 00:56:01,407
I was wrong.

453
00:56:19,093 --> 00:56:21,226
What are you doing?

454
00:56:22,496 --> 00:56:24,198
Anna.

455
00:56:24,298 --> 00:56:26,664
Don't touch me!

456
00:56:28,936 --> 00:56:32,504
You know, maybe this writing gig's
just a bit too much pressure for you.

457
00:56:34,108 --> 00:56:37,742
- I can't stay here tonight.
- Oh, God.

458
00:56:40,114 --> 00:56:42,750
- I'm gonna stay in town.
- You serious?

459
00:56:42,850 --> 00:56:46,053
- We'll talk tomorrow.
- Okay, well, listen.

460
00:56:46,153 --> 00:56:49,821
Take these. Have a good night's sleep.

461
00:57:14,415 --> 00:57:15,426
(GRUNTS)

462
00:57:32,733 --> 00:57:34,599
(CAR BEEPS)

463
00:57:43,010 --> 00:57:44,545
JOE: Who is it?

464
00:57:44,645 --> 00:57:49,281
It's Anna. We met this afternoon.
I need to talk to you.

465
00:57:56,757 --> 00:57:58,993
I'm closed.

466
00:57:59,293 --> 00:58:02,360
You can come by again in the morning.

467
00:58:03,130 --> 00:58:05,096
Are you sure?

468
00:58:08,736 --> 00:58:10,653
These are all handcrafted

469
00:58:11,605 --> 00:58:14,230
from various tribes.

470
00:58:15,175 --> 00:58:17,778
Some from my own family, in fact.

471
00:58:17,878 --> 00:58:19,947
(HITS DRUM)

472
00:58:20,547 --> 00:58:22,783
Some I just picked up over the years.

473
00:58:23,440 --> 00:58:25,152
Let me know if you're interested
in anything

474
00:58:25,252 --> 00:58:27,454
and I'm sure we could work out
some kind of a discount.

475
00:58:27,854 --> 00:58:30,024
Could we just start the session?

476
00:58:30,124 --> 00:58:31,990
Yeah, of course.

477
00:58:33,994 --> 00:58:36,061
Why don't you, um...

478
00:58:37,130 --> 00:58:39,898
pick one of these stones.

479
00:58:41,402 --> 00:58:43,935
- This one?
- Sure.

480
00:58:45,903 --> 00:58:47,406
Good choice.

481
00:58:53,013 --> 00:58:54,615
(MUSIC PLAYING)

482
00:58:55,015 --> 00:58:58,485
- Really?
- I don't have a free hand for the drums.

483
00:58:59,185 --> 00:59:01,019
This will work just fine.

484
00:59:04,158 --> 00:59:06,691
Just relax.

485
00:59:10,831 --> 00:59:12,926
Why don't you, uh...

486
00:59:13,500 --> 00:59:15,602
take off your top.

487
00:59:16,102 --> 00:59:18,626
You gotta be kidding me.

488
00:59:20,975 --> 00:59:23,809
Do you want me to help you or not?

489
00:59:26,380 --> 00:59:29,747
(SIGHS)
You've gotta be fucking kidding me.

490
00:59:31,251 --> 00:59:33,537
Now lay down.

491
00:59:36,156 --> 00:59:38,022
(RATTLING)

492
01:00:05,786 --> 01:00:07,764
Now...

493
01:00:10,924 --> 01:00:13,828
We'll search for the chakra

494
01:00:14,728 --> 01:00:17,261
with the most negative energy.

495
01:00:30,811 --> 01:00:32,707
(RATTLING)

496
01:00:34,448 --> 01:00:36,282
Whoa.

497
01:00:38,218 --> 01:00:39,785
What was that?

498
01:00:41,922 --> 01:00:43,425
What just happened?

499
01:00:46,426 --> 01:00:47,693
What was that?

500
01:00:49,697 --> 01:00:51,734
Do you ever, uh...

501
01:00:52,099 --> 01:00:55,664
feel a growing pressure in your chest
when you... when you dream?

502
01:00:56,570 --> 01:01:00,972
A feeling of numbness in your limbs
almost as if you were paralyzed?

503
01:01:01,308 --> 01:01:03,106
