Well, why would I?
The police will be here in a minute.

585
01:11:11,463 --> 01:11:14,287
Great, then you can tell them
what happened to Vera Palm.

586
01:11:14,687 --> 01:11:15,755
What?

587
01:11:15,855 --> 01:11:18,521
The blind woman who mysteriously
went missing out on the salt lake.

588
01:11:18,651 --> 01:11:20,093
Who you keep pretending not to know

589
01:11:20,193 --> 01:11:23,463
although her dog
is standing right over there.

590
01:11:27,067 --> 01:11:30,804
Yeah, he dug this up
out on the salt lake.

591
01:11:31,104 --> 01:11:36,594
So tell me, Paul. How did she go missing
if her guide dog was out there with her?

592
01:11:51,157 --> 01:11:52,710
Vera was my wife.

593
01:11:59,466 --> 01:12:02,333
She was a very talented, but, um...

594
01:12:03,703 --> 01:12:05,872
unsuccessful architect.

595
01:12:05,972 --> 01:12:08,839
This house was supposed
to change all of that.

596
01:12:10,944 --> 01:12:15,113
For two years, the only thing she did
was work on this project.

597
01:12:16,816 --> 01:12:19,086
Day in, day out.

598
01:12:19,486 --> 01:12:22,589
She became obsessed with the place.

599
01:12:22,689 --> 01:12:25,858
And by the time she laid
the foundations...

600
01:12:25,958 --> 01:12:30,026
(SIGHS) ...we were living
completely separate lives.

601
01:12:33,099 --> 01:12:35,033
We were like complete strangers.

602
01:12:40,974 --> 01:12:44,041
She invited me out here to celebrate
when it was completed.

603
01:12:44,978 --> 01:12:47,480
VERA ON PHONE:
Paul? Are you still there?

604
01:12:47,580 --> 01:12:49,082
PAUL'S VOICE: But why would I?

605
01:12:49,182 --> 01:12:51,851
VERA ON PHONE: I wanted you
to come out and celebrate.

606
01:12:51,951 --> 01:12:54,585
PAUL'S VOICE:
This house had stolen my wife.

607
01:12:56,456 --> 01:12:58,126
VERA ON PHONE:
I can't believe you're doing this.

608
01:13:00,093 --> 01:13:01,472
Paul?

609
01:13:02,262 --> 01:13:03,528
Paul, are you still there?

610
01:13:05,965 --> 01:13:07,832
On the way home that night...

611
01:13:09,669 --> 01:13:12,205
she fell asleep at the wheel

612
01:13:12,605 --> 01:13:14,839
from sheer exhaustion.

613
01:13:17,510 --> 01:13:20,713
When they found the car,
they said, um...

614
01:13:20,813 --> 01:13:23,680
that she was lucky because...

615
01:13:24,017 --> 01:13:27,885
the Joshua tree she hit
stopped her from going over the cliff.

616
01:13:29,856 --> 01:13:32,857
But a branch came in
through the windscreen and, um...

617
01:13:35,395 --> 01:13:37,263
blinded her.

618
01:13:37,563 --> 01:13:39,766
Then what happened?

619
01:13:40,166 --> 01:13:41,732
I became her scapegoat.

620
01:13:45,204 --> 01:13:48,773
If I didn't already feel guilty,
she made me feel guilty.

621
01:13:52,712 --> 01:13:55,295
She didn't miss a chance

622
01:13:55,892 --> 01:13:58,345
to make me feel her pain.

623
01:14:00,920 --> 01:14:04,454
I really tried,
but I just couldn't imagine...

624
01:14:06,259 --> 01:14:09,493
being her caretaker
for the rest of my life.

625
01:14:14,901 --> 01:14:18,171
So when she started to get better,

626
01:14:18,938 --> 01:14:21,405
I got her the dog.

627
01:14:22,875 --> 01:14:26,276
And she came to live out here
by herself.

628
01:14:28,748 --> 01:14:31,982
My life was finally
becoming normal again.

629
01:14:34,587 --> 01:14:37,453
And then something fantastic happened.

630
01:14:39,726 --> 01:14:42,349
I met someone new.

631
01:14:43,029 --> 01:14:46,397
Someone I could fall in love with again.

632
01:14:53,906 --> 01:14:57,674
Then Vera called me
one day and said, uh...

633
01:14:58,177 --> 01:15:00,813
said she wanted me to come out here

634
01:15:00,913 --> 01:15:02,813
to discuss something.

635
01:15:04,250 --> 01:15:07,810
It was the best time we'd had
for over a year.

636
01:15:09,555 --> 01:15:12,725
Anyway, by the time
we got to the salt lake,

637
01:15:12,825 --> 01:15:15,513
I realized what it was all about.

638
01:15:17,597 --> 01:15:21,334
She said she wanted
to move back to Los Angeles,

639
01:15:22,034 --> 01:15:25,104
have another go at our marriage.

640
01:15:25,204 --> 01:15:27,941
It was the last thing I wanted to hear.

641
01:15:28,458 --> 01:15:31,008
So I told her about us.

642
01:15:31,944 --> 01:15:34,614
She was furious.

643
01:15:34,714 --> 01:15:37,417
She said she would divorce me.

644
01:15:37,517 --> 01:15:41,421
I would lose everything.
All my savings, the house.

645
01:15:41,521 --> 01:15:44,424
She said she would ruin me
if I didn't stay with her.

646
01:15:44,624 --> 01:15:47,807
Who wouldn't side with a blind woman
whose husband had cheated on her?

647
01:15:49,028 --> 01:15:51,893
I couldn't let that happen.

648
01:15:56,469 --> 01:15:58,488
You killed her.

649
01:16:05,678 --> 01:16:07,716
We'd, um...

650
01:16:10,216 --> 01:16:14,684
we'd walked quite a long way
into the salt lake.

651
01:16:17,256 --> 01:16:19,523
And I just, um...

652
01:16:21,594 --> 01:16:24,228
took the dog and kept on walking.

653
01:16:25,765 --> 01:16:28,331
They never found her body.

654
01:16:31,370 --> 01:16:33,046
This happened on March 2nd.

655
01:16:34,040 --> 01:16:35,541
Yeah.

656
01:16:35,941 --> 01:16:37,711
And Jeremy knew.

657
01:16:37,811 --> 01:16:40,613
He saw me coming home without Vera.

658
01:16:40,713 --> 01:16:43,780
Started asking some questions.

659
01:16:45,218 --> 01:16:48,252
But an illegal immigrant
is easy to keep quiet.

660
01:16:48,921 --> 01:16:50,924
You have to tell the police, Paul.

661
01:16:51,724 --> 01:16:53,242
No, I'm not gonna let her ruin my life.

662
01:16:53,342 --> 01:16:56,729
No, you don't understand. You have to,
all right? It's the only way she'll stop.

663
01:16:57,129 --> 01:16:58,564
What are you talking about?

664
01:16:58,664 --> 01:17:02,935
It was Vera that killed Jeremy
and she's gonna come after you next.

665
01:17:03,035 --> 01:17:05,238
Have you gone completely nuts?

666
01:17:05,338 --> 01:17:07,173
(SIGHS)

667
01:17:07,273 --> 01:17:09,490
If you don't tell the police, I will.

668
01:17:10,676 --> 01:17:12,712
Well, be my guest.

669
01:17:12,812 --> 01:17:14,664
I can't wait to see the expression
on their faces

670
01:17:14,764 --> 01:17:18,287
when a... a drug-abusing writer
with a history of mental illness

671
01:17:18,387 --> 01:17:23,688
tells them that my ex-wife's ghost
is on some kind of revenge mission.

672
01:17:32,848 --> 01:17:34,367
I'll let you do the talking.

673
01:17:34,667 --> 01:17:37,303
PAUL'S VOICE: She said she would
ruin me if I didn't stay with her.

674
01:17:37,903 --> 01:17:43,139
Who wouldn't side with a blind woman
whose husband had cheated on her?

675
01:17:46,279 --> 01:17:48,912
Don't let her do this to us.

676
01:17:55,788 --> 01:17:57,855
Don't let her separate us, Anna!

